2. Immediate introduction of a peacekeeping force consisting of
                            contingents from the US and Brazil to
                            verify the ceasefire and ensure the separation of forces;

5. End of military administration and start of local self-government by
                            the local councils with the Contact Group ratifying all decisions not
                            inconsistent with the purposes of the Agreement;

6. Phased withdrawal of British forces, with the peacekeeping force to
                            assume responsibility for the security of the islands for a limited
                            period;

7. Negotiations, without preconditions, on the definitive settlement of
                            the dispute with the assistance of the other members of the Contact
                            Group;
